question: Katie had 7 pages of math homework and 3 pages of reading homework. If each page had 9 problems on it, how many problems did she have to complete total?
response:
Katie had 7 pages of math homework, and each page had 9 problems. So, she had to complete 7 x 9 = <<7*9=63>>63 math problems.
She also had 3 pages of reading homework, and each page had 9 problems. So, she had to complete 3 x 9 = <<3*9=27>>27 reading problems.
In total, Katie had to complete 63 + 27 = <<63+27=90>>90 problems.
The answer is 90.
